cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.MM 

This paper is about visual tracking, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category. The paper also proposes a novel algorithm that combines two different tracking methods, which involves machine learning and optimization techniques. Therefore, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely categories. The proposed algorithm also involves particle filtering, which is a common technique in robotics and control systems. Therefore, cs.RO (Robotics) is another possible category. Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed algorithm on a dataset of video sequences, which involves multimedia analysis and processing. Therefore, cs.MM (Multimedia) is another possible category.
